SIMPLE: grill
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grill
<hw>Grill</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>gril</ets>. See
<er>Grill</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
gridiron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[They] make <qex>grills</qex> of [wood] to broil their meat.</q>
<rj><qau>Cotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is broiled on a gridiron, as meat, fish,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A figure of crossed bars with interstices, such as
those sometimes impressed upon postage stamps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A grillroom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Grill
<hw>Grill</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Grilled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Grilling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>griller</ets>, fr.
<ets>gril</ets> gridiron, OF. <ets>gra⟦ium⟧l</ets>, L.
<ets>craticulum</ets> for <ets>craticula</ets> fine hurdlework, a small
gridiron, dim. of crates hurdle. See <er>Grate</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To broil on a grill or gridiron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Boiling of men in caldrons, <ex>grilling</ex> them on
gridirons.</q> <rj><qau>Marvell.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To torment, as if by broiling.</def>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To stamp or mark with a grill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Grill
<hw>Grill</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To undergo the process of being
grilled, or broiled; to broil.</def></p>

<p><q>He had <qex>grilled</qex> in the heat, sweated in the rains.</q>
<rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grillade</ent>⟦br⟧
